<div class="defense-section">
  <h3>The One Principle That Stays Constant</h3>
  <p>Every AI capability that expands what agents can do autonomously requires a proportional investment in oversight, containment, and reversibility. The security implications scale with capability. A chat AI that gives wrong answers needs guardrails. An autonomous agent that executes transactions needs human approval workflows. An agent that controls physical systems needs safety interlocks and manual override at every decision point.</p>
  <p>The governance question is always the same: <strong>what is the maximum harm this system can cause before a human has the opportunity to intervene — and is that harm acceptable?</strong></p>
</div>

